{"key":"processedPost-9377736","value":{"id":9377736,"first":9368106,"last":9380092,"when":1228578176,"utime":"12/06/08 05:42 PM","content":"Don't worry about it.&nbsp; Make up for any losses by misting. Multiple light mistings are superior to fewer heavy mistings. If you're really worried, run a cool mist in the room as recommended.<br /><br />One possible cause is the tray is blocking the moisture from being able to evaporate off the perlite.&nbsp; Raise the tray on shot glasses too.<br /><br />You should also 'rake' the damp perlite with your fingers to form ridges and valleys that will increase the surface area, thus increasing humidity.<br /><br />Bottom line, don't cover holes if they're 1/4\".&nbsp; Simply mist to make up the difference.&nbsp; Fresh air is the number 1 pinning trigger.<br />RR","title":"Re: Can't seem to get humidity above 90%","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}